 not Zamtil, however, I will make you pay for undue flames (though well thought out flames are always welcome).<br><br>Warrior Alternate Experience Enhancements<br><br>First, I would like to flat out state that I am well aware of the feelings of the development and design team towards me, my playstyle, and my philosophy in regards to Everquest. With that being said, amongst my many criticicisms, I have always been firm in my beliefs that you are all competent and well versed in the design and development of EQ. In short, I have stood by your decisions and continued to play this game far longer than 99% of your gaming demographic.<br><br>Now, onto the matters at hand. Warrior class skills in the AA system are 100% useless and do not in any way, shape, or form, represent what a warrior in the game of Everquest embodies. I will not lie to you and tell you that I was not bitter about being snubbed out of yet another beta - Not even given the chance to help make at the very least my class more viable going into Luclin. So now, through a third party, I bring you my proposal.<br><br>1)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Bodyshield: With this skill a warrior is able to target another player and completely encompass them, taking ALL hits that player may receive during the duration of the discipline. <br>A)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Activatable/Hotkeyed<br>B)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp 15-30 Minute Recycle Time<br>C)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Once a warrior “latches” on to a player, the warrior cannot do anything but take hits until the discipline wears off or the warrior is slain. He may not attack, he may not taunt, he simply becomes a rather large “rune” of sorts.<br>D)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The skill should have 3 levels. Level 1) Duration of 9 seconds; Level 2) Duration of 15 seconds; Level 3) Duration of 20 seconds. Point costs of 3/6/9 per Class AA guidelines.<br><br>2)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Shield Mastery: To give the class some diversity and to also make use of the myriad shields available in game, I suggest a skill known as Shield Mastery. Shield Mastery allows a warrior to STUN mobs previously unstunnable, MUCH like the Paladin AA Class Skill. The format is as follows.<br>A)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Three tiered system. Level 1 Shield Mastery allows for a warrior to stun HUMANOID sized creatures between levels 55-57. Level 2 Shield Mastery allows for a warrior to stun HUMANOID sized creatures between levels 58-59. Level 3 Shield Mastery allows a warrior to stun HUMANOID sized creatures between levels 60-62. The AA format is again, 3/6/9.<br>B)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp To avoid people trying to shortcut shield mastery, the skill will be its own separate hotkey that requires the warrior to have wielded a SHIELD for 1.5 mins before the hotkey becomes active. Thus once a warrior wears a shield and wants to take advantage of Shield Mastery, they will have to actually have a shield equipped for nearly 2 mins before they can begin utilitizing the skill.<br>C)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Additionally, benefits a warrior with shield mastery will receive will be a 2/5/10% bonus to PARRY.<br><br>3)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Domination of Will: In short, this is a much needed upgrade to the TAUNT skill. The skills reuse time is 15 seconds. Each use of DoW will add +500 hate to the user, cumulative. Point cost: 5 Class Points.<br><br>4)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Glancing Blow: The cornerstone of the warrior class skills. This skill will be innate, it will have a prerequisite of both Combat Mitigation at lvl 3 and Combat Agility at lvl 3. It’s function is as follows: Level 1) The warrior has a 2% chance for any blow landing upon him to do 40% less damage. At Level 2) The warrior has a 5% chance for any blow landing upon him to do 45% less damage. At Level 3) The warrior has a 10% chance for any blow landing upon him to do a full 50% less damage. The Tier Requisites will be 6/9/12 points. Thus, for a warrior to MAX Glancing Blow, he will have to have spent 12+12+6+9+12, (51 Points).<br><br>5)&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Frontal Stun Immunity: For 9 class points, a warrior can choose to train to be unstunnable from the front, much like an Ogre. The Prerequisite for this skill is Level 1 Combat Agility. I would like to point out that in beta and in early final, and even in Kunark, frontal stun was never an issue. There were never balance problems with the innate class skill Ogres had, HOWEVER, given the ability of mobs to stun without bash a la Kunark, and the snowball effect throughout expansions with mobs that flurry constantly and rampage, ALL non Ogre warriors are terribly marginalized. Had we known when Everquest first went live that this would have been such an issue, I’m certain many of us would have no doubt gone the route of the Ogre Warrior. Of course, YOU yourselves did not know the imbalance this would cause this late in the game – nevertheless, it exists, it’s not balanced, it needs a remedy. This is a boon for Ogres as they do not have to spend the 11 points necessary to gain this ability and a boon for the thousands of us NON-Ogres who desperately need this ability. Please give this some consideration.<br><br>That is all I have to write for now. I can be reached at furor_foh@yahoo.com if any further questions are required. I am also always willing to help out when asked. I’m not the huge jerk you think I am… thanks for your time.<br><br>Alex<br>Player of Furor Planedefiler<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ugeentrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geen Trueblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 2:11:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors in Luclin - Read Up - Commentary/Criticism welc</span><hr size=1> I like the shield one, but maybe it should be a melee arch type ability. As a Paladin I know how much this type of skill has been sought after. It just makes sense that using a shield increase at least one of your avoidance skills. Also, Shadow Knights could use the stun ability as well. Personally us Paladins probably don't need ANOTHER stun ability, but hell, they already given us more then we need, I don't think one more is gonna hurt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/unazbuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nazbuk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/alien.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 2:35:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://megaman.retrofaction.com/imagery/protoman1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors in Luclin - Read Up - Commentary/Criticism welc</span><hr size=1> If the shield master skill went to melee who normally used a shield then it would be overpowering. This is good for warriors because I can't think of one warrior who's used a shield since he got dual wield. <br><br>Everything in the list looks good. What do you think the chances of VI even thinking about putting something like this in or fixing the current system for warriors? <br><br>Later<br> <p>Nazbuk <BR> <img src=http://megaman.retrofaction.com/imagery/x4slash.gif> <BR>Ring of Shadows - Veeshan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/utrindade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trindade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 2:57:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.optushome.com.au/ahonnibal/smolderthumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors in Luclin - Read Up - Commentary/Criticism welc</span><hr size=1> I think all these class skills sound great. The cost sounds like it's definitely in line with the abilities.<br><br>Except one thing to add is that warriors should have the bard/knight &quot;Physical Enhancement&quot; skill, and should also get a skill that raises our dodge/parry/riposte to slightly exceed that of monks (eg: must have avoidance: 3 costs 3/6/9 to raise dodge/parry/riposte to the equivelant of 5 skill levels higher than monks for each respectively. ie: 3 to raise dodge, then 6 for parry, and 9 for riposte). If monks get rogue damage now, why should they absorb damage better than warriors?<br><br>They could easily scrap that warcry/ae taunt/rampage/bind wound crap to introduce these. <p>Trindade<br>60th level warrior<br><b>Master potion user</b><br><a href=http://www.bladesofwrath.com>Blades of Wrath</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uzoldarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zoldarf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 3:05:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors in Luclin - Read Up - Commentary/Criticism welc</span><hr size=1> Anything that makes shields worthwhile would be a boon.  Stunning would be a good idea.  Maybe have shield mastery give some sort of bonus to the AC from the shield as well.  Or let you swing more often with your primary weapon if you're wielding a shield.  Or lets you bash more often.  All kinds of things can be done here.<br><br>As for frontal stun immunity, I think all warriors should get this automatically after a certain level, without having to invest in any AA points.  Even if it was level 60.  Ogres would have an advantage all the way up to that level, and then things would pare out.  Of course, I play a dwarf, so I'm biased, but it's just bizarre that one race has an ability that makes them inherently better at a class (not counting stat points).  I think kick starts stunning mobs at 54, which helps mitigate the kick/slam disparity between small and large races... I don't see why the same can't be done with the frontal stun issue.<br><br>As for taunt, maybe have the upgraded version put you on top of the hate list by a hundred points or so, instead of just barely on top of the list.<br><br>Another idea would be to have an ability that adds to the AC bonus you get from every point of AC on your gear.  This would have to be expensive in terms of ability points, but tanking is what warriors are all about... may as well have abilities that make warriors more effective at doing their job.<br><br>I see where you're going with the &quot;rune&quot; idea... it would let the warriors not doing the main tanking something to do... ie take the heat for a cleric who just topped the hate list, etc.  That seems like a very overpowering ability though.. unless there was some major downside to using it.  Maybe not let the warrior attack for a minute or so AFTER the effect has run out.<br><br>All good ideas... better than some of the garbage they have now, that's for sure.<br><br>-Zoldarf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uneoxen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NeoXen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 3:30:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors in Luclin - Read Up - Commentary/Criticism welc</span><hr size=1> Well I remember the &quot;Warriors and Frontal Stun&quot; topic that made quite a stir over on the old noows site, and at the time I thought it was very well thought out and written. <br><br>For the most part there was a resounding agreement to that post.<br><br>That being said, there wasn't a doubt in my mind that VI would step back and see the &quot;big picture&quot; with where the game is now, take into consideration the facts presented, and add this as an AA skill. Expansion hits the shelves, and nothing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>As for the other skills they sound pretty interesting too. Though like the poster above said, what are the chances of VI doing anything? To me it feels more like a &quot;corporate-run&quot; game now, not so much a &quot;player-run&quot; game.  <br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I will not lie to you and tell you that I was not bitter about being snubbed out of yet another beta<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>/sarcasm on <br><br>What do you mean you were snubbed out of beta, you (and the rest of us) are in it now. I'm still waiting for SoL to go live. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>/sarcasm off<br><br>Hopefully the dev/QC teams are taking a look at these types of posts, and, should they feel there's merit in them, consider ways to implement them in-game.<br><br>/shrug . . . we'll see.<br><br>~Late <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> divex</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 4:54:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Your ideas seem well thought out and not overpowering.<br>Except for the rune idea.<br>This could eliminate many aggro problems that certain classes need to be aware of.<br>Also, verant wants enchanters new spells of decreasing aggro to be used.<br>Also, with the increased taunt, I dont think verant would like it since they also want enchanters aggro increasing spells to be used. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uneckrosofrallos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neckros of Rallos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 5:34:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> A fine idea... maybe you want to look at a class that has TRUELY poor skills tho, aka enchanter.... heh <p>Neckros Dundee"That's not a knife..."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ugstermactruckk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gster MacTruckk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.lindas.com/trains/ez_ani11.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 6:52:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.e