 including warriors, AA skills more toys then anything else. And, also, warriors should have been made unstunnable starting at 60 from day one of velious. It is demeaning to have a nice foot tall, 2-ton glob of crap tanking better then my sexy Halfling self. <br><br>Good post, I hope verant is paying attention<br><br>Alfan Fat<br>60 Warlord, Veeshan<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uashesemberblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ashes Emberblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/14/02 9:22:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Too overpowering.</span><hr size=1> The rune idea, as stated earlier, is too overpowering.  It would make the enchanter aggro spells (although fairly useless now) even more useless.  Giving high aggro classes a &quot;Get out free&quot; card such as that wouldn't be balancing, unless there was a significant downside for the warrior.  Doubling the damage taken might make it balanced, or perhaps coupling that with a crippling or slowing effect if the warrior survived.<br><br>The frontal stun immunity would be an excellent addition, but it's a rather moot point at this stage in the game.  Ogres were given an ability with few uses upon the game's release, but gained a bit more functionality with the release of two subsequent expansions.  However, frontal stuns have never been the class shattering problem, at least to me, you have purported Furor.  Ample pretaunt time and proper aggro control more than make up for stuns, even on flurrying mobs.<br><br>When I read your post, it vaguely reminds me of the &quot;Everquest should get this, this, this&quot; post that pops up on the Safehouse every once in a while.  The post lists several changes that should be made to the game that benefit the player with very little in the way of balance or negative consequences.  I agree with your sentiment, however, the warrior has become less the master of arms and battle, and more the masochistic punching bag.<br><br>Ashes Emberblade<br>Dark Elven Warlord<br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.kabald.org">Kabald</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uvaclavromanov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaclav Romanov</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 2:28:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Too overpowering.</span><hr size=1> I think for the most part those ideas you pitched above would be excellent additions, but unfortunately, I doubt VI is going to retool the AA system other than possibly touching up the existing skills...<br><br>I especially like the Shield Mastery... warriors with a reason to use a shield over dual wield would be awesome for those that want to take that route.(although I wouldn't worry about the humanoid only thing)<br><br>And I don't know the exact hate numbers anywhere near as you likely do, but +500 every 12-15 sec seems a little excessive... the same every 20-30 sec would seem a little more on target IMO... especially if this would be an additional taunt button...<br><br>Another to add I just semi-brainstormed(at 5AM in the morning mind you so it might have problems that would make it unusable) would be a 'stance' type ability for an AA choice, which when active would root the player, but reduce their melee damage taken - spell damage would be amplified(since you wouldn't be dodging it at all) and Fear would overwrite the effect(to prevent that obvious exploit) - perhaps instant use/reuse but takes 3-5 sec to get into and out of stance.. <br><br>Honestly, when I first heard of /disc stonestance for monks that was my initial concept of what it did...<br><br>Anywho, hopefully you do get some tuning to the AA skills from VI from your feedback, it seems almost all classes need their choices improved... I do think it's more likely to get them to retool current abilities to be more useful before they code new ones however...<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ucandiemandarkryder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Candieman Darkryder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 3:37:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.castletrash.com/animation/plani131.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Too overpowering.</span><hr size=1> As always great and insightful thoughts on how to better our class Furor. Realistically i could see VI adding the immunity to stun from the front and glancing blow....which i reall dig the idea of glancing blows. <p><left><img src="http://watchersrealm.virtualave.net/eq_sigs/eq_sig_stwc.jpg"></left><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71256">Solanthious</a>-60 Warlord<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71260">Inshackles</a>-16 Enchanter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ugrimmlokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 3:45:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Too overpowering.</span><hr size=1>  I just want taunt mastery. Make taunt work more often and on things over 65. <p><B><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6122>Grimmlokk</a>, Forlorn</B> <BR>Warlord of E'ci<BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/Grimmlokk/fullsize/bunnysig.jpg><BR><B><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7932>Pokewell Andoften</a>, Forlorn </B><BR>Blackguard of the 57th pilfer<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uphantron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 5:41:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors in Luclin - Read Up - Commentary/Criticism welc</span><hr size=1> Okay, I'm a newbie to the high end game, but it seems to me that Verant is not about to make changes that'd trivialize encounters with AA, and yet your proposed changes will, or at least can.<br><br>The problem with the skills you suggested is that they're too certain.  Assuming the shield mastery stun % isn't something impossibly rare, you can have a high confidence of stunning the mobs that shield mastery can effect by throwing enough warriors at it.  As I understand, warriors aren't exactly the primary damage output in a raid situation, so what's to stop the non MT warriors switch to a shield 2 minutes before the fight will end to get the stun in at the end?  Like I said, I don't know the high end game well, but presumably you made this suggestion because it'd help dealing with unstunnable mobs that gate/CH/whatever.  But if you've enough people with this skill, then stunning becomes a near certainty, and that'd trivialize the encounter.<br><br>OTOH, if the % to stun is impossibly rare that even with all your warriors with shield mastery you can't guaranteed a stun, then people'd just go back to the ways.  Guilds dealed with unstunnable mobs before there was Luclin, and they'll just go back to those methods.  You'd end up with a skill no one bothers to put point in since I assume stun is supposed to be the biggest part of shield mastery.  <br><br>Likewise, Domination of Will by what you wrote is a taunt that always work (at least that's my understanding of it).  I'm pretty sure EverQuest's hate list works in a deterministic fashion, i.e. what got you on the hate list once will do the same again under the identical conditions.  I understand MT is the primary way to take down uber mobs, and it seems unlikely Verant will give Warriors a nearly guaranteed way to stay on the top of the hatelist.  If someone found out how to stay on top of the hatelist using DoW, then it will always work as long as others remember what they did, and you're back to a scripted encounter, which I think Verant is trying to avoid.<br><br>If you meant for DoW to have a chance of adding 500 aggro, then I stand corrected.  However, I think it's more likely that Verant will add a taunt that does random aggro seeing how the AA has a lot of similar things.  Critical heal/mend clearly increase a class's power, but you just can't count on having a critical heal or mend to save someone from dying.  I suspect if a new taunt is given via AA, it'd be along the same lines as the critical stuff from AA.<br><br>The other suggestions sounds good though, but I think Bodyshield may have balance implications.  Balance is a tough thing to achieve.  I understand you want to have things that improve the warrior class without making encounters trivial, but just because an exploit using the changes isn't readily obvious doesn't mean it isn't there.  And all it takes is one person to figure out how to use a seeming innocent balance change to exploit/trivialize encounters to ruin the game for everyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/utindel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tindel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 6:14:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors in Luclin - Read Up - Commentary/Criticism welc</span><hr size=1> &quot;, I will make you pay for undue flames (though well thought out flames are always welcome).&quot;<br><br>hahaha <br><br><br>Oh and nice skills there, especially the shield mastery. <br><br> <p><A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22658>Tindel</A>Dark Templars - Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Razinelius</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 6:49:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Good ideas</span><hr size=1> These are good ideas.  Most if if not all can be worked in the game as is or with deemed necessary balancing changes by VI.  The only point I disagree on is JUST giving other NONogre races immunity to stun from front. IF you're gonna give that to all other races, THEN give Ogres something EXTRA as an innate ability that others don't have please. Example: an EXTRA 1 or 2 save VS mag PER every lvl gained from day one.<br><br>I'm all up for giving people of other races what was currently OUR privellege, but don't leave us with an empty space... just fill it with something else that OTHER races will not envy as much yet will still be useful to us in game.<br><br>Razinelius<br>Ogre Warrior<br>Transcendent Order<br>RZ <br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/umerauk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merauk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 10:58:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.elementofdarkness.com/images/member/Merauk/Kitty.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good ideas</span><hr size=1> Using AA points to increase haste for warriors would have been interesting.  Totally agree on the frontal stun immunity though it creates an incredible void between Ogres and everyone else.<br><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.elementofdarkness.com/Eqi/inv.asp?char=7">Merauk Soulripper</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>Phantasmist Cazic Thule<br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.elementofdarkness.com">Element of Darkness</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uremfin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Remfin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 11:14:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good ideas</span><hr size=1> &quot;I will not lie to you and tell you that I was not bitter about being snubbed out of yet another beta&quot;<br><br>Uhm, isn't this the same person who told the world he was done with EQ and never coming back?  You can't beta test if you refuse to play! <p>Remfin<BR>Level 60 Sorceror<BR>Terris - Thule<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/umilodruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milodruid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/15/02 12:15:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ffiresofheaven32084frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good ideas</span><hr size=1> Ogres pay for their un-stunability.  We are big, fat ugly, cant climb cliffs or fit thru doors.  To merely give this ability to all warriors would not be fair.  You want to not get stunned from the front play an ogre.  You make it sound like ogres are &quot;given&quot; this ability over other classes.  Thats simply not true.   We have other disabilities to make up for it.  Playing an ogre is more difficult by far than playing a barb.<br><br>Bodyshield:<br>I HATE how mobs can hit you thru the floor or ceiling.<br>I have always felt that a mob should NOT be able to hit a person standing behind a warrior.  Perha